# QuantLab Landing Web Rules

## Read First

Before editing the public landing surface, read:

- `@.agents/project-brief.md`
- `@.agents/implementation-rules.md`
- `@.agents/current-state.md`
- `@docs/brand-guidelines.md`
- `@docs/landing-governance.md`
- `@landing/AGENTS.md`

## Source Of Truth

- Keep public positioning in `docs/brand-guidelines.md`.
- Keep landing ownership and workflow in `docs/landing-governance.md`.
- Keep rendered copy, layout, and styling in `landing/`.

## Change Discipline

- Make the smallest landing change that satisfies the task.
- Do not duplicate hero copy, taglines, or palette decisions across files without a single canonical owner.
- Do not expand the public landing into product logic, CLI logic, or broker logic.
- Keep GitHub Pages deployment pointing at `landing/` only.
- Preserve the current brand architecture unless the task explicitly changes it.

## Quality Rules

- If copy changes, verify it still matches the brand guide.
- If layout or styling changes, keep the page readable on desktop and mobile.
- If the public web surface changes, avoid introducing alternate naming systems or second-brand variants.
